                            <comment id="13941" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Tue, 19 Jul 2005 08:05:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That&apos;s a bit odd: Unnamed MethodInvokingJobDetailFactoryBean definitions should actually receive a generated bean name, which is the class name plus a counter. That generated id should in turn be used for the JobDetails. Hence, I&apos;m a bit puzzled why this doesn&apos;t generate unique ids out of the box.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14009" author="robh" created="Wed, 20 Jul 2005 23:53:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is caused by the fact that anonymous inner beans are NOT given unique identities by Spring. I have added a fix to CVS for this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14168" author="johan" created="Sun, 31 Jul 2005 22:52:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Works great now. Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
